Date:  0/0/2001
Source:  NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page:  No., 49/76
Edition:
Quote:  Climbing ferns are much less dominant in New Zealand bush than in tropical rainforest, but mokimoki (<i>Microsorum scandens), Rumohra adiantiformis</i> and thread fern (<i>Blechnum filiforme</i>) are common throughout, while jointed fern (<i>Arthropteris tenella</i>) and mangemange (</i>Lygopodium articulatum</i>) are characteristic of the warmer northern forest.
